Introduction

Avlo Version: 4.1 

    * This readme will help you install avlo to the av3xx. This bootloader features a config file based menu (a bit like LILO) loader. It is designed to be light and fast.
    * Special features:
          o use a config file to read the OS list and options
          o default OS launched after a specified time-out
          o can launch ajz or bin file
          o failsafe mode: when a problem is detected in the config file, the device is automatically put in usb mode and wait to be rebooted
          o when usb is connected, you can enter usb mode, by pressing F3
          o safe shutdown, HD spindown is performed now before stopping the device
          o customizable, skinable interface
          o battery status meter 


Navigation/Control
UP/DOWN, ON or RIGHT	to launch an OS
F3			enter USB mode
OFF			perform a safe shutdown



    * The installation process is the same as for the bootloader or winav. The main steps are:
      1. transform the cjbm.ajz to a bin file (if you want a faster load of archos firmware)
      2. backup the original firmware
      3. copy this binary, avlo.ajz and avlo.img to the HD
      4 update to avlo
      5. put back the original ajz file 


Detailed installation:

    * 1. transform the cjbm.ajz to a bin file
      go on rockbox project and grab their descrambler:
      http://rockbox.haxx.se/tools/descramble.exeexternal link
          o use this tool to transform the cjbm.ajz you use to a binary file
          o avlo can also launch ajz file, so you can always start archos firmware if you put back the original cjbm.ajz file after installing avlo 
    * 2. backup the original firmware
          o be sure to keep a copy of the cjbm.ajz file from archos on your computer 
    * 3. copy this binary and avlo.ajz and avlo.img to the av3xx HD
          o rename avlo.ajz to cjbm.ajz and put it on the root folder of the av's HD
          o copy the binary version of archos firmware to the same folder
          o copy the avlo.cfg to the same folder, don't forget to edit this file to match your config, see the section on avlo.cfg format 
    * 4. update to avlo
          o boot the device and do an update. At reboot you'll be in avlo (archos firmware can warn you that you have a bad cjbm.ajz file when you boot) 
    * 5. put back the original ajz file
          o for some reason you should put back the cjbm.ajz file from archos on the HD. 



avlo.cfg format

    * First look at the sample file provided in the package. The avlo.cfg format is simple, for each OS you want to use, you need to specify the image location (image=...) and a label (label=...). Image files can be .bin or .ajz.
          o Example: to add an OS which binary is /linux/kernel.bin and you want to named it Linav 

image=/linux/kernel.bin
label=Linav

    * For the linux kernel you can add the append= param to specify the myinit you want to use. It is an optional parameter, if you don't use it, the default myinit (/mnt/myinit) will be used. the format of this param is append=..path to myinit.... So a valid config for linux kernel: 

image=/linux.bin
label=Linav
append=/mnt/myinit

          o Note: quotes (") are required if you want to put spaces: to add archos FW: with the binary: /archos.bin and the label Archos FW 

image=/archos.bin
label="Archos FW"

    * You can also add some general options:
          o default: the label (not the image) of the default OS to be launched
          o time-out: timeout before launching the default OS (if specifyed)
                + warning, this is not in seconds, numbers > 10000 should be used 
          o repeat: repeat rate of key 


    * Defining a skin:
          o You can define a custom skin for AvLo 

bg_img="/avlo_gnu4b.img"

                + please read AvLo_Skin_README for creating a custom skin 
    * Comments:
          o Comments can be defined by preceding a line of text with a # 

#commented text is ignored ;-)
An Example avlo.cfg:

# Menu list
image=/cjbm.bin
label="Archos FW bin"

image=/CJBM.AJZ
label="Archos FW"

image=/avlo.ajz
label="AvLo test ajz"

image=/avlo.bin
label="AvLo test bin"

# general options
# default action
default="Archos FW bin"
# Repeat key rate
repeat=10000
# Time out before launching default
time-out=25000

#bg_img="/avlo_steel.img"
bg_img="/avlo.img"
